 Police officers in Homa Bay have apprehended
a man for allegedly transporting 73 brooms of cannabis sativa, mostly known as
bhang. The suspect, Sylvanus Okeyo was nabbed on
Tuesday afternoon at Nyabomo village in Suba South. According to the National Police Service (NPS),
the suspect who was conveying the herb on a motorcycle was intercepted by
officers acting on a tip-off along the Magunga-Nyabera road. The officers recovered the illegal drugs
concealed in form of 73 brooms then stacked in a sack. As NPS expressed confidence in the fight
against drug trafficking, it appreciated public efforts of remaining vigilant
and reporting drug peddling cases.  “Our sincere gratitude to the members
of the public for continuously sharing information with us, as we rid our
society off illicit brews, hard drugs and other social factors causing crime,”
NPS stated.